üü¢ BASIC LEVEL (15 Questions)
1. What is Spring Framework and why do we use it?

Answer:

Spring is a lightweight Java framework for building enterprise applications.

Provides IoC (Inversion of Control) and DI (Dependency Injection).

Use Case:
Banking app service layer decoupled from DAO using DI.

Common Mistake: Saying ‚ÄúSpring is only for web apps‚Äù.

Follow-up: What problems does Spring solve compared to EJB?

Tip: Say loosely coupled, testable, maintainable.

2. What is IoC and DI?

Answer:

IoC: Control of object creation is given to Spring container.

DI: Dependencies are injected by Spring.

@Service
class PaymentService {
   private final OrderService orderService;
   public PaymentService(OrderService orderService){
       this.orderService = orderService;
   }
}

Mistake: Confusing DI with service calling service.

Follow-up: Constructor vs Setter injection?

Tip: Always prefer constructor injection.

3. What are Spring Bean scopes?

Singleton (default)

Prototype

Request

Session

Application

Use case: Request scope for HTTP request data.

Mistake: Using prototype for stateless service.

Follow-up: Why singleton is safe?


4. What is Bean lifecycle?

Instantiate

Populate dependencies

init()

ready to use

destroy()

@PostConstruct
public void init(){}

@PreDestroy
public void cleanup(){}


5. @Component vs @Service vs @Repository

@Component ‚Äì generic

@Service ‚Äì business logic

@Repository ‚Äì persistence + exception translation

Follow-up: What is exception translation?


6. @Autowired vs @Qualifier vs @Primary

@Autowired ‚Äì auto injection

@Qualifier ‚Äì specify bean

@Primary ‚Äì default bean


7. What is Spring Boot?

Opinionated framework

Removes boilerplate configuration

Embedded servers (Tomcat)


8. What is Auto Configuration?

Spring Boot automatically configures beans based on classpath.

Example: Add spring-boot-starter-data-jpa ‚Üí Hibernate auto-configured.


9. application.properties vs YAML

.properties ‚Üí key=value

.yml ‚Üí hierarchical

server:
  port: 8081

10. What is Spring MVC architecture?

Flow:
Client ‚Üí DispatcherServlet ‚Üí Controller ‚Üí Service ‚Üí DAO ‚Üí Response


11. What is REST?

Stateless

Resource based

HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)



12. What is @RestController?

Combination of:

@Controller + @ResponseBody


13. What is Spring Data JPA?

Simplifies database operations

Provides JpaRepository

interface UserRepo extends JpaRepository<User, Long> {}

14. What is @Transactional?

Manages DB transactions.

Mistake: Using it on private methods.


15. JAR vs WAR deployment

JAR ‚Üí embedded server

WAR ‚Üí external server


üü° INTERMEDIATE LEVEL (20 Questions)
1. Constructor vs Setter Injection

Constructor ‚Üí mandatory dependency

Setter ‚Üí optional

Best Practice: Constructor injection.


2. What is AOP?

Aspect Oriented Programming separates cross-cutting concerns.

Examples:

Logging

Security

Transactions


3. What are AOP terminologies?

Aspect

Advice

JoinPoint

Pointcut


4. How does Spring Boot Auto Config work internally?

Uses @EnableAutoConfiguration

Reads spring.factories


5. What is DispatcherServlet?

Front controller that routes all HTTP requests.


6. Difference between @ControllerAdvice & @ExceptionHandler

@ControllerAdvice ‚Äì global exception

@ExceptionHandler ‚Äì specific


7. What is DTO?

Data Transfer Object used between layers.


8. What is Hibernate?

ORM tool that maps Java objects to database tables.


9. Lazy vs Eager Loading

Lazy ‚Üí load when needed

Eager ‚Üí load immediately


10. What is N+1 problem?

Multiple queries fired when fetching relationships.


11. What is Pagination?
